    "body": "### Problem\n\nFor non-traditional targets such as WASM/webassembly, and for remote-ssh, a VFS (virtual filesystem) layer may be a way to run Nvim \"mostly\" on one machine, while routing some operations to another.\n\n\nReferences \n\n- node.js is adding a VFS layer which may be a useful reference: https://github.com/nodejs/node/pull/61478\n\nRelated:\n\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/35567\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/21635\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/discussions/37822\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nidk",
